Explore the design of a video frame buffer that is clocked
with 75 MHz by the read-out logic, but should be written
by the microprocessor, which runs at 50 MHz. The dual-ported
block RAM inside the FPGA cannot be used, because it is
too small. Assume that the clocks are not totally unrelated,
but are produced by a digital clock manager, which aligns
raising clock edges if possible.
